Steel buttplate

OEM canvas/leather sling

Norinco stamped Chinese markings - Arsenal cartouche (three characters in a triangle = factory code 116) and set of three Chinese ideographs on the side of the receiver that translate to: “Type 56”).
Also Engraved:
B-West L.A. CA.
7.62x39mm Sporter
Made in China by Norinco

Serial Numbers: 1105138	 on the frame
45078		on the bolt
45078		on the firing pin assembly
45078		on the back of the receiver cover
45078		on the trigger guard
45078		on the magazine
(all numbers match)
Indecipherable stamping on the receiver below wood line (very faint - could be 08, 68, 88?)
Milled trigger group has an assortment of miscellaneous marks

I put maybe 40 rounds at most through it.
Very little use and the action shows it.
Carried as a back up gun for deer hunting.
I bought used around 1985.
I don't know the date of manufacture, but if the serial number was coded the same way as used by the /26\ Jianshe Arsenal, it would be 1967. Definitely post 1963.
The considerable amount of grime in the stock and the fact that the engraving is over the blueing leads me to believe this is Chinese military surplus (military rifles all factory code).
It think is misleading for B-West to have called this unmodified PLA stock military surplus rifle a "Sporter"

Very good condition. Wood stock has a few dings, missing finish in spots, but no cracks, gouges, or repairs. Minor pitting. A great shooting rifle.

The Remington R51 Handgun is a modern version of Remington's original Model 51, designed in 1915 by John Pedersen. The Model 51, considered ahead of its time, became one of General George Patton's personal side-arms during World War II. The Remington R51 Handgun modernizes and updates Pedersen's design to work with 9mm Luger and .40 Smith & Wesson cartridges while maintaining the personality, shooting characteristics and size of the original. The R51 averages 25% less muzzle flip with the lowest bore axis in the industry. It has intuitive pointing characteristics with optimized grip angle. This highly concealable pistol with a match-grade 3.4" barrel and bushing handles +P factory ammunition. It uses a hammer-fired, Pedersen action with a locked breech and fixed 416 stainless steel barrel. The slim, aluminum frame has 25-lines-per-in. checkering on the front grip strap and drift-adjustable sights.
